    <title>Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United States relating to contributions and expenditures with respect to Federal elections.</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2018-01-19</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Constitutional Amendment</b></p> <p>This joint resolution denies as protected speech any financial expenditures, or in kind equivalents, with respect to a candidate for federal office, without regard to whether or not a communication expressly advocates the election or defeat of a specified candidate in the election.</p> <p>The resolution gives Congress the power to enact a mandatory public financing system to provide funds to qualified candidates in federal elections, which shall be the sole source of funds raised or spent with respect to federal elections.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-02-12T21:38:12Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <updateDate>2018-01-19T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
